<details class="wp-block-details is-style-default" style="border-bottom-width:1px;margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--md);padding-right:0;padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--md);padding-left:0"><summary>Does the Single site license allow development sites?</summary><!-- wp:paragraph {"placeholder":"Type / to add a hidden block"} -->
<p>Yes, local and staging development sites are allowed to use the Single license. You will receive an extra development license free to use on your development sites.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></details>
<!-- /wp:details -->
<!-- wp:details {"style":{"spacing":{"padding":{"top":"var:preset|spacing|md","bottom":"var:preset|spacing|md","left":"0","right":"0"},"margin":{"top":"0","bottom":"0"}},"border":{"bottom":{"width":"1px"}}},"className":"is-style-default","expandIcon":"plus"} -->
<details class="wp-block-details is-style-default" style="border-bottom-width:1px;margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--md);padding-right:0;padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--md);padding-left:0"><summary>How to install the Blockify Pro plugin?</summary><!-- wp:paragraph {"placeholder":"Type / to add a hidden block"} -->
<p>Installing the Blockify Pro plugin is as easy as uploading the blockify-pro.zip file you receive upon purchasing Blockify Pro membership. Once the plugin ZIP file has been installed and activated, you can head to the Editor and enter your Blockify Pro API key to receive automatic plugin updates and cloud access.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></details>
<!-- /wp:details -->
<!-- wp:details {"style":{"spacing":{"padding":{"top":"var:preset|spacing|md","bottom":"var:preset|spacing|md","left":"0","right":"0"},"margin":{"top":"0","bottom":"0"}},"border":{"bottom":{"width":"1px"}}},"className":"is-style-default","expandIcon":"plus"} -->
<details class="wp-block-details is-style-default" style="border-bottom-width:1px;margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--md);padding-right:0;padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--md);padding-left:0"><summary>Can I use my own child theme?</summary><!-- wp:paragraph {"placeholder":"Type / to add a hidden block"} -->
<p>Yes, it is recommended to always use a child theme with Blockify (and Blockify Pro). A child theme is a safe way to customize your WordPress site without losing your changes due to theme updates. Blockify provides multiple child themes to help you get started, or start from scratch using a free plugin like Create Block Theme.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></details>
<!-- /wp:details -->
<!-- wp:details {"style":{"spacing":{"padding":{"top":"var:preset|spacing|md","bottom":"var:preset|spacing|md","left":"0","right":"0"},"margin":{"top":"0","bottom":"0"}},"border":{"bottom":{"width":"1px"}}},"className":"is-style-default","expandIcon":"plus"} -->
<details class="wp-block-details is-style-default" style="border-bottom-width:1px;margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--md);padding-right:0;padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--md);padding-left:0"><summary>Is Blockify Pro a theme or a plugin?</summary><!-- wp:paragraph {"placeholder":"Type / to add a hidden block"} -->
<p>Blockify Pro is a WordPress plugin. It requires the free Blockify theme and/or any Blockify child theme. Once the Pro plugin is activated on your site, all of the premium features will be available in the WordPress block editor.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></details>
<!-- /wp:details -->
<!-- wp:details {"style":{"spacing":{"padding":{"top":"var:preset|spacing|md","bottom":"var:preset|spacing|md","left":"0","right":"0"},"margin":{"top":"0","bottom":"0"}},"border":{"bottom":{"width":"1px"}}},"className":"is-style-default","expandIcon":"plus"} -->
<details class="wp-block-details is-style-default" style="border-bottom-width:1px;margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--md);padding-right:0;padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--md);padding-left:0"><summary>How do I log in to the BlockifyWP website?</summary><!-- wp:paragraph {"placeholder":"Type / to add a hidden block"} -->
<p>Currently Pro members do not need to log into the https://blockifywp.com site. All Pro information, including the Blockify Pro plugin and private Slack group invitation are available in your LemonSqueezy order.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></details>
<!-- /wp:details -->
<!-- wp:details {"style":{"spacing":{"padding":{"top":"var:preset|spacing|md","bottom":"var:preset|spacing|md","left":"0","right":"0"},"margin":{"top":"0","bottom":"0"}},"border":{"bottom":{"width":"1px"}}},"className":"is-style-default","expandIcon":"plus"} -->
<details class="wp-block-details is-style-default" style="border-bottom-width:1px;margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--md);padding-right:0;padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--md);padding-left:0"><summary>How to access Pro blocks?</summary><!-- wp:paragraph {"placeholder":"Type / to add a hidden block"} -->
<p>Simply install and activate the Blockify Pro plugin on your site, then enter your license key. Once the license has been added, all of the Pro blocks will be available in the block editor.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></details>
<!-- /wp:details --></div>
<!-- /wp:column -->
<!-- wp:column {"verticalAlignment":"top","style":{"position":{"all":"relative"}}} -->
<div class="wp-block-column is-vertically-aligned-top"><!-- wp:details {"style":{"spacing":{"padding":{"top":"var:preset|spacing|md","bottom":"var:preset|spacing|md","left":"0","right":"0"},"margin":{"top":"0","bottom":"0"}},"border":{"bottom":{"width":"1px"}}},"className":"is-style-default","expandIcon":"plus"} -->
<details class="wp-block-details is-style-default" style="border-bottom-width:1px;margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--md);padding-right:0;padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--md);padding-left:0"><summary>Which icons are included in Pro?</summary><!-- wp:paragraph {"placeholder":"Type / to add a hidden block"} -->
<p>Blockify Pro includes more SVG icon font families for blocks that support Blockify icons. The current icon sets included in Pro are Heroicons, Feathericons, Iconic icons and Phosphor duotone icons. More icon sets can be added upon request. Custom icon sets can also be added by including the files in your own child themes /assets/icons/{icon-set}/{icon-name}.svg directory.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></details>
<!-- /wp:details -->
<!-- wp:details {"style":{"spacing":{"padding":{"top":"var:preset|spacing|md","bottom":"var:preset|spacing|md","left":"0","right":"0"},"margin":{"top":"0","bottom":"0"}},"border":{"bottom":{"width":"1px"}}},"className":"is-style-default","expandIcon":"plus"} -->
<details class="wp-block-details is-style-default" style="border-bottom-width:1px;margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--md);padding-right:0;padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--md);padding-left:0"><summary>Which Google fonts are included in Pro?</summary><!-- wp:paragraph {"placeholder":"Type / to add a hidden block"} -->
<p>All variable Google fonts are included with Pro. Currently only variable fonts are supported.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></details>
<!-- /wp:details -->
<!-- wp:details {"style":{"spacing":{"padding":{"top":"var:preset|spacing|md","bottom":"var:preset|spacing|md","left":"0","right":"0"},"margin":{"top":"0","bottom":"0"}},"border":{"bottom":{"width":"1px"}}},"className":"is-style-default","expandIcon":"plus"} -->
<details class="wp-block-details is-style-default" style="border-bottom-width:1px;margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--md);padding-right:0;padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--md);padding-left:0"><summary>How can I enable automatic dark mode?</summary><!-- wp:paragraph {"placeholder":"Type / to add a hidden block"} -->
<p>Simply place the Dark Mode Toggle block anywhere on a page or template and automatic dark mode will be enabled. Once added, the visitors browser preference will be automatically detected and your site will switch to the users preferred mode.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></details>
<!-- /wp:details -->
<!-- wp:details {"style":{"spacing":{"padding":{"top":"var:preset|spacing|md","bottom":"var:preset|spacing|md","left":"0","right":"0"},"margin":{"top":"0","bottom":"0"}},"border":{"bottom":{"width":"1px"}}},"className":"is-style-default","expandIcon":"plus"} -->
<details class="wp-block-details is-style-default" style="border-bottom-width:1px;margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--md);padding-right:0;padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--md);padding-left:0"><summary>How to access Pro patterns?</summary><!-- wp:paragraph {"placeholder":"Type / to add a hidden block"} -->
<p>Simply install and activate the Blockify Pro plugin on your site, then enter your license key. Once the license has been added, all of the Pro patterns for the active theme will be available in the block editor. </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></details>
<!-- /wp:details -->
<!-- wp:details {"style":{"spacing":{"padding":{"top":"var:preset|spacing|md","bottom":"var:preset|spacing|md","left":"0","right":"0"},"margin":{"top":"0","bottom":"0"}},"border":{"bottom":{"width":"1px"}}},"className":"is-style-default","expandIcon":"plus"} -->
<details class="wp-block-details is-style-default" style="border-bottom-width:1px;margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;padding-top:var(--wp--preset--spacing--md);padding-right:0;padding-bottom:var(--wp--preset--spacing--md);padding-left:0"><summary>How do I create a child theme?</summary><!-- wp:paragraph {"placeholder":"Type / to add a hidden block"} -->
<p>We recommend using the create block theme plugin to create your own child themes. With a little know-how, they can be the perfect way to build your own website. They inherit all of the parent theme's design which saves you a tonne of work and provides a head start for your next project.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></details>
<!-- /wp:details -->
